# Esiana Plugins

Applies to `plugins/` and `backend/src/lib/plugins/`. Author docs: [docs/plugin-development/](../../../docs/plugin-development/). Engineering: [data-interceptors.md](../../docs/plugins/data-interceptors.md).

## Manifest v2

- `permissions[]` — declare only what the plugin needs
- `engines.esiana-core` — version range; mismatch auto-disables at load
- `configSchema` — inline or `config-schema.json` for settings UI

## Registration

- `register(router, context)` via `PluginHostContext`
- Routes validated at register time (namespace firewall, blocked infra prefixes)
- Campaign-scoped data via `createPluginDataService(campaignId)` when permitted

## Data interceptors

- Worker sandbox, allowlists, `failMode`, quarantine on failure
- No unrestricted main-thread plugin code for intercept paths

## UI integration

- Declarative UI slots with error boundaries (header, sidebar, map, settings)
- `wiki:decorate` — read-only `metadata` / `pluginDisplay` injection on wiki responses
- `extendRoutes` skipped for content lifecycle; do not bypass core ACL

## Integrations vs core product

Foundry sync and similar packages are **stubs/adapters**, not core VTT features. Do not move combat/tactical simulation into core to support them.

